Small hive beetle infestation (_Aethina tumida_), Costa Rica
----------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 24 Aug 2015 from Dr Bernardo Jaen Hernandez, Director General, Servicio Nacional de Salud Animal (SENASA), Ministerio de Agricultura y Ganaderia, Barreal de Heredia, Costa Rica

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 21 Aug 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 24 Aug 2015
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Aethina tumida_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: La Garita, Santa Cecilia, La Cruz, Guanacaste
Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Aug 2015
Outbreak status: resolved 24 Aug 2015
Epidemiological unit: Apiary
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Bees (hives) / 3 / 1 / 0 / 3 / 0
Affected population: The event has occurred in a sentinel apiary (3 hives) strategically located near the northern border with epidemiological surveillance purposes.

Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Bees (hives) / 33.33 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent / 100 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
[but see below]

Epidemiological comment: The event has been detected near [in fact exactly across] the border with Nicaragua, where the disease was previously reported in 2014.
[see map in OIE summary of 1st report from Nicaragua at:
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=14888. - Mod.JW]

Note by the OIE World Animal Health Information and Analysis Department: Since this is the 1st time that small hive beetle infestation (_Aethina tumida_) has been identified in the history of the country, the reason for notification as 1st occurrence applies to the country, but the event is in fact limited to a zone.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; disinfection/disinfestations; traceability; quarantine; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; zoning; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Laboratory of the veterinary Services (national laboratory) / Bees / optical microscopy / 24 Aug 2015 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

